quran[18]{c,v,t}:
  7,109,"Said the chiefs of Pharaoh's people, 'Verily, this is surely a knowing magician"
  7,110,he desires to turn you out of your land; - what is it then ye bid
  7,111,"They said, 'Give him and his brother some hope; and send into the cities to collect"
  7,112,and bring you every knowing magician
  7,113,"And the magician came to Pharaoh and said, 'Is there indeed a reward for us if we are conquerors"
  7,114,"He said, 'Yea! and ye shall be of those who draw nigh unto me"
  7,115,"They said, 'O Moses! wilt thou cast down (thy rod) or shall we be (first) to throw"
  7,116,"Said he, 'Throw down;' and when they threw down, they did enchant the people's eyes, and made them dread, and brought a mighty magic"
  7,117,"But we inspired Moses (saying), 'Throw down thy rod, and it will gulp down that which they devise"
  7,118,"and the truth stood fast, and vain was that which they had done"
  7,119,"and they were conquered there, and turned back feeling small"
  7,120,and the magicians threw themselves down adoring
  7,121,"Said they, 'We believe in the Lord of the worlds"
  7,122,the Lord of Moses and Aaron
  7,123,"Said Pharaoh, 'Do ye believe in him ere I give you leave? This is craft which ye have devised in the land, to turn its people out therefrom, but soon shall ye know"
  7,124,"I will cut off your hands and your feet from opposite sides, then I will crucify you altogether"
  7,125,"They said, 'Verily, we unto our Lord return"
  7,126,"nor dost thou take vengeance on us, save for that we believe in the signs of our Lord, when they come to us. 'O our Lord! pour out upon us patience, and take us to Thyself resigned"